1
00:00:07,050 --> 00:00:08,310
Edolas...?

2
00:00:08,310 --> 00:00:12,420
Yes, Edolas... A different 
world than this one.

3
00:00:13,110 --> 00:00:16,600
Over there, the world has 
begun losing its magic.

4
00:00:17,420 --> 00:00:19,420
Losing magic?

5
00:00:19,420 --> 00:00:20,790
Say what?

6
00:00:20,790 --> 00:00:22,380
What's that mean?

7
00:00:22,380 --> 00:00:26,610
Unlike this world, in 
Edolas, magic is limited.

8
00:00:26,890 --> 00:00:30,500
If people use too much of it, it'll 
eventually vanish from the world.

9
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:14,190
When resources began to dry up, Edolas's 
king made a decision to save their magic...

10
00:02:14,190 --> 00:02:18,960
He invented a magic spell that would absorb 
magic from another world, namely this one.

11
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:23,110
Yes... It's the Hyperspace Magic, Anima.

12
00:02:24,060 --> 00:02:27,000
It's what that hole in the sky was.

13
00:02:27,250 --> 00:02:29,780
That's... Anima?

14
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:32,930
Anima?!

15
00:02:32,930 --> 00:02:35,340
No, it'll be dangerous to come with me.

16
00:02:41,170 --> 00:02:42,480
Edolas.

17
00:02:46,570 --> 00:02:49,380
The plan started 6 years ago,

18
00:02:49,380 --> 00:02:52,670
and Anima were opened at various 
places around this world,

19
00:02:52,670 --> 00:02:55,360
but it didn't produce the 
results they expected.

20
00:02:56,580 --> 00:03:00,200
Someone was going around 
and closing the Anima...

21
00:03:04,470 --> 00:03:10,360
When I heard the story from Wendy 
about Jellal, I mean Mystogan,

22
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:12,810
I didn't think it was possible, but...

23
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,300
I'm sure of it now. It was him.

24
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:23,270
But the Anima this time was simply too 
large for anyone to defend against it,

25
00:03:23,270 --> 00:03:25,160
and the guild was absorbed.

26
00:03:25,940 --> 00:03:28,610
Why did they suck up Fairy Tail?

27
00:03:29,020 --> 00:03:30,020
Didn't I tell you?

28
00:03:31,050 --> 00:03:33,690
This is all for Edolas's magical power.

29
00:03:34,710 --> 00:03:37,910
There are a ton of powerful 
wizards at Fairy Tail!

30
00:03:37,910 --> 00:03:39,480
Is that why it was targeted?

31
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:41,450
Yes.

32
00:03:42,330 --> 00:03:45,320
Man, how selfish can you get?

33
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:48,550
Give everyone back, you jerk!

34
00:03:51,220 --> 00:03:52,210
Damn it...

35
00:03:55,010 --> 00:04:00,590
So this... is Carla's and my fault?

36
00:04:00,590 --> 00:04:02,240
Indirectly, yes.

37
00:04:02,490 --> 00:04:04,970
Indirectly?

38
00:04:04,970 --> 00:04:11,930
We were sent to this world from the Kingdom 
of Edolas with a separate mission.

39
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,230
That can't be!

40
00:04:15,230 --> 00:04:19,260
You were born from an egg... In this world!

41
00:04:19,260 --> 00:04:22,520
So was Happy! I found him!

42
00:04:23,270 --> 00:04:24,350
True.

43
00:04:25,950 --> 00:04:30,720
Just so you know, I've 
never set foot in Edolas.

44
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:35,800
Like Wendy said, I was born 
and raised in this world.

45
00:04:36,590 --> 00:04:42,300
But knowledge of Edolas and our 
mission was ingrained in us.

46
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:47,780
We should have known it all 
from the moment we were born.

47
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:50,800
And yet...

48
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:54,820
Why don't you know anything?

49
00:04:58,880 --> 00:04:59,990
I...

50
00:05:08,010 --> 00:05:09,790
So that's that.

51
00:05:10,140 --> 00:05:15,620
We're from Edolas, and what 
happened here is our fault.

52
00:05:15,850 --> 00:05:19,580
You said something about 
a separate mission, Carla?

53
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:23,190
I can't say.

54
00:05:25,530 --> 00:05:30,690
Please tell me, Carla! I 
want to know what I am!

55
00:05:31,020 --> 00:05:35,520
I told you, I can't say! You 
have to remember yourself!

56
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:46,990
Righto!

57
00:05:46,990 --> 00:05:50,700
We've got everything settled, so let's go!

58
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:51,900
Off to this Edolas place!

59
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:53,600
Everything is hardly settled!

60
00:05:54,540 --> 00:05:56,880
You don't understand at all...

61
00:05:57,140 --> 00:05:58,660
Natsu-san...

62
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:03,580
Natsu... I...

63
00:06:04,930 --> 00:06:07,260
All this unease is making me hungry.

64
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:10,360
That just proves you're alive!

65
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:21,430
Everyone's in Edolas, right? In 
that case, we gotta go save 'em!

66
00:06:21,940 --> 00:06:23,450
What about that, Carla?

67
00:06:23,670 --> 00:06:26,820
They might be there...

68
00:06:27,330 --> 00:06:30,470
But I don't know if we could save them.

69
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:36,970
I don't even know if we 
could return from Edolas...

70
00:06:38,630 --> 00:06:43,890
Well, as long as my friends aren't 
here, I don't need to come back.

71
00:06:44,460 --> 00:06:46,630
Everyone except for Igneel, anyway...

72
00:06:47,870 --> 00:06:49,050
I agree.

73
00:06:51,100 --> 00:06:54,640
Can we really save everyone?

74
00:06:58,210 --> 00:07:03,340
I guess I'm basically a 
member of Fairy Tail too...

75
00:07:03,660 --> 00:07:08,080
And I do feel somewhat responsible 
about what my home Kingdom has done...

76
00:07:08,340 --> 00:07:11,220
I guess I might take you there...

77
00:07:12,290 --> 00:07:14,320
But you need to promise me a few things.

78
00:07:14,660 --> 00:07:19,660
Returning to Edolas is a 
violation of my orders.

79
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:24,000
We can't be discovered by 
the people from the Kingdom.

80
00:07:24,550 --> 00:07:26,590
Everyone has to be in disguise.

81
00:07:26,590 --> 00:07:27,930
Me, too?

82
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,590
You sure about this, Carla?

83
00:07:30,590 --> 00:07:33,250
Yes. I've made up my mind.

84
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:38,590
And you, he-cat... Don't 
ask me about our orders.

85
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,310
Aye...

86
00:07:40,980 --> 00:07:46,520
And thirdly, I don't know anything 
other than basic info about Edolas.

87
00:07:46,830 --> 00:07:48,840
I can't guide you.

88
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:49,310
Got it.

89
00:07:49,310 --> 00:07:50,190
Roger that.

90
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:53,460
Finally...

91
00:07:54,400 --> 00:08:00,910
If I or the he-cat do something to 
betray you, do not hesitate to kill us.

92
00:08:09,100 --> 00:08:12,310
I wouldn't do something like that...

93
00:08:12,310 --> 00:08:13,760
And would you shut that thing up!

94
00:08:21,030 --> 00:08:22,110
Let's go.

95
00:08:22,550 --> 00:08:24,410
He-cat, grab onto Natsu.

96
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:26,020
We're going to fly there?

97
00:08:26,020 --> 00:08:28,020
Our wings...

98
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:31,230
Our wings are for returning to Edolas.

99
00:08:34,030 --> 00:08:37,760
Let's go, Happy! To your home country!

100
00:08:39,910 --> 00:08:40,860
Aye!

101
00:08:46,210 --> 00:08:49,370
He-cat, open up your full magical power!

102
00:08:49,370 --> 00:08:50,940
Aye, sir!

103
00:08:53,510 --> 00:08:56,640
We can enter Edolas through the 
remaining traces of the Anima!

104
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:59,690
We'll cut through with our wings, Aera!

105
00:09:08,730 --> 00:09:09,590
Now!

106
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:45,320
So bright...

107
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:21,360
This is... Edolas...

108
00:10:22,050 --> 00:10:25,010
My roots...

109
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:44,130
The islands are floating.

110
00:10:44,130 --> 00:10:47,180
This is your homeland, Happy.

111
00:10:47,470 --> 00:10:48,990
This is Edolas.

112
00:10:50,070 --> 00:10:51,370
It really is...

113
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:53,690
...a different world...

114
00:10:54,890 --> 00:10:58,010
It's full of strange trees and plants!

115
00:10:58,010 --> 00:11:01,940
Wow! Look at that, Happy!

116
00:11:02,170 --> 00:11:04,400
A river is flowing in the sky!

117
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,620
How's it do that?

118
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:07,770
Come on, you people...

119
00:11:07,770 --> 00:11:11,590
I know how you feel, but we 
didn't come here to sightsee.

120
00:11:11,590 --> 00:11:13,700
Don't get so excited.

121
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:16,000
Yeah, you're right.

122
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,280
My bad...

123
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:27,590
My wings suddenly...

124
00:11:27,910 --> 00:11:29,410
What happened?

125
00:11:29,410 --> 00:11:30,620
I told you, remember?

126
00:11:30,620 --> 00:11:33,370
You can't use magic freely here.

127
00:11:33,630 --> 00:11:35,850
Oh, you're right!

128
00:11:35,850 --> 00:11:38,110
I feel kind of strange...

129
00:11:39,510 --> 00:11:41,230
Okay then!

130
00:11:41,230 --> 00:11:43,300
Let's go search for everyone!

131
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:48,880
Natsu, where exactly should we be searching?

132
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:50,110
Leave it to me!

133
00:11:50,110 --> 00:11:52,100
I can rely on my nose for something like...

134
00:11:53,140 --> 00:11:53,970
Huh?

135
00:11:54,310 --> 00:11:55,900
It's no use.

136
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:58,650
There's so many things I've never smelled 
before, I can't tell what's what.

137
00:12:01,230 --> 00:12:02,490
You're right.

138
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:05,780
The air tastes a little different, too...

139
00:12:05,780 --> 00:12:08,300
Does that mean fire'll taste different, too?

140
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:10,120
Don't ask me, thank you.

141
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:12,420
And I'm hungry!

142
00:12:12,420 --> 00:12:14,740
We should have packed lunches...

143
00:12:14,740 --> 00:12:16,720
Is this any time to be relaxed, people?!

144
00:12:17,430 --> 00:12:20,630
Anyway, where are we walking toward?

145
00:12:20,630 --> 00:12:21,900
Who knows...

146
00:12:21,900 --> 00:12:24,960
For now we'll walk, and we'll 
get somewhere eventually.

147
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:27,140
That's not going to solve anything.

148
00:12:27,140 --> 00:12:29,130
We don't have any other way.

149
00:12:29,130 --> 00:12:30,810
It can't be helped.

150
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:35,520
Now look here, you!

151
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:36,930
That was me, actually.

152
00:12:36,930 --> 00:12:40,370
Anyway, there's no one here...

153
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:43,160
It's just one big forest.

154
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:45,720
Even so, we need to get in disguises.

155
00:12:46,020 --> 00:12:48,410
Sure, but how?

156
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:53,270
Hey...

157
00:12:53,270 --> 00:12:54,390
Natsu...

158
00:12:54,390 --> 00:12:56,250
I really don't think so...

159
00:13:03,870 --> 00:13:07,310
This isn't a disguise, it's camouflage!

160
00:13:07,310 --> 00:13:11,300
Whatever! What's important is 
that no one finds us, right?

161
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:12,970
Don't sweat it.

162
00:13:12,970 --> 00:13:16,550
This is kind of embarrassing...

163
00:13:16,550 --> 00:13:20,030
I can't say much for your fashion 
sense, but the idea has its merits.

164
00:13:21,540 --> 00:13:22,890
Really?

165
00:13:24,850 --> 00:13:26,880
I'm kind of hot...

166
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:29,440
These leaves are stuffy.

167
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,730
You're pitiful.

168
00:13:30,730 --> 00:13:31,820
Deal with it.

169
00:13:31,820 --> 00:13:33,540
Aye...

170
00:13:40,130 --> 00:13:42,170
It's that weird river from before!

171
00:13:42,170 --> 00:13:44,990
I can't believe that a river 
is flowing into the sky!

172
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:48,350
Oh, right! I was hungry!

173
00:13:48,350 --> 00:13:49,890
I said, deal with it!

174
00:13:52,030 --> 00:13:55,980
I bet that river is filled with yummy fish...

175
00:13:57,190 --> 00:13:58,630
Look, over there!

176
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:00,900
It looks like an Edolas human.

177
00:14:01,870 --> 00:14:05,180
Phew... He looks like us.

178
00:14:05,180 --> 00:14:07,300
What did you imagine they'd look like?

179
00:14:07,300 --> 00:14:10,420
And he's fishing, of all things!

180
00:14:10,420 --> 00:14:11,560
I'm jealous...

181
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:13,350
By the way, where's Natsu-san?

182
00:14:13,350 --> 00:14:14,100
Yo!

183
00:14:15,580 --> 00:14:17,310
Got a sec?!

184
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:19,580
Natsu-san...

185
00:14:19,580 --> 00:14:21,060
What are you doing?!

186
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:23,000
Yeah, that's definitely scary...

187
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:26,480
I'm searching for this 
guild named Fairy Tail.

188
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:28,200
Have you seen them around somewhere?

189
00:14:31,210 --> 00:14:32,680
Hey, wait!

190
00:14:32,680 --> 00:14:34,290
What's wrong with him?

191
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:36,410
I just asked a little question...

192
00:14:36,410 --> 00:14:37,750
What were you thinking?

193
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:41,120
You're wearing a weird outfit, 
then ask about "Fairy Tail"?

194
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:43,480
How's he supposed to know what that means?

195
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:46,730
How else are we gonna find 
out where everyone is?

196
00:14:46,730 --> 00:14:47,820
Well, in that case...

197
00:14:48,070 --> 00:14:51,450
If that man goes and 
reports to the Kingdom...

198
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:54,580
This camouflage is pointless, isn't it?

199
00:14:54,580 --> 00:14:57,440
Anyway, we have to hurry and find everyone.

200
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:59,460
Phew, finally cooled off.

201
00:14:59,460 --> 00:15:03,980
Too bad that person didn't 
leave his fishing rod behind...

202
00:15:04,310 --> 00:15:05,930
Did I do something?

203
00:15:05,930 --> 00:15:09,340
Anyway, that's a strange sound...

204
00:15:09,770 --> 00:15:11,240
Another fisherman?

205
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,540
All right! This time, I'll...

206
00:15:12,540 --> 00:15:14,950
You just don't learn, do you?

207
00:15:17,060 --> 00:15:19,220
Look, it's a fish!

208
00:15:19,220 --> 00:15:20,470
All right!

209
00:15:20,470 --> 00:15:22,650
We'll catch it and have a meal...

210
00:15:23,300 --> 00:15:24,980
It's huge!

211
00:15:25,580 --> 00:15:26,470
Looks delicious!

212
00:15:26,470 --> 00:15:27,580
And huge!

213
00:15:27,580 --> 00:15:29,590
Ooh, a big, strong fella!

214
00:15:29,590 --> 00:15:30,610
I'm gettin' fired up!

215
00:15:30,610 --> 00:15:33,490
But Natsu-san... We have 
to get going before...

216
00:15:33,490 --> 00:15:36,070
I'll only need 3 seconds.

217
00:15:38,170 --> 00:15:40,790
Iron Fist of the Fire Dragon!

218
00:15:41,730 --> 00:15:42,540
Huh?

219
00:15:44,540 --> 00:15:45,540
Natsu-san!

220
00:15:46,380 --> 00:15:47,470
Huh?

221
00:15:47,470 --> 00:15:48,900
My fire don't work...

222
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:50,040
I told you, remember?

223
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:53,390
You can't use magic freely in Edolas!

224
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:54,680
Which means...

225
00:15:54,680 --> 00:15:56,220
We run!

226
00:15:59,180 --> 00:16:00,890
It's still chasing us!

227
00:16:01,450 --> 00:16:04,170
Not being able to use magic is 
gonna be a real pain, isn't it?

228
00:16:04,170 --> 00:16:07,360
It's a little late to 
realize that now, Natsu!

229
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:09,860
Anyway, middle of the forest or not,

230
00:16:09,860 --> 00:16:12,360
isn't making such a big scene 
gonna get us in trouble?

231
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:15,200
Tell that to the giant catfish!

232
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:18,230
Oh, crap!

233
00:16:18,230 --> 00:16:19,570
It's a dead-end!

234
00:16:19,570 --> 00:16:21,400
Happy, fly me!

235
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:23,420
I can't use magic, remember?

236
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:32,290
Dang!

237
00:16:32,290 --> 00:16:34,530
This is what happens when 
we can't use magic?!

238
00:16:34,780 --> 00:16:36,680
Is everyone okay?

239
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:39,920
I'm hungry, but otherwise still alive.

240
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:42,660
Give it a rest already, okay?

241
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:46,730
We're not in disguise, so don't 
cause any more commotion!

242
00:16:46,730 --> 00:16:47,730
Carla...

243
00:16:48,310 --> 00:16:50,820
My fault? Really?

244
00:16:50,820 --> 00:16:52,820
Not entirely, but for the most part!

245
00:16:53,380 --> 00:16:58,650
I don't know what the Kingdom would 
do if they found out we're here.

246
00:16:58,650 --> 00:17:01,430
In that case, I couldn't predict 
what would happen to us,

247
00:17:01,430 --> 00:17:04,290
let alone whether we'd 
be able to save everyone!

248
00:17:04,290 --> 00:17:06,230
I-I see...

249
00:17:06,450 --> 00:17:09,500
I don't really understand, 
but it's my fault, I guess...

250
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:12,400
What don't you understand about it?

251
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:14,470
Carla, you're going too far.

252
00:17:14,470 --> 00:17:17,130
Natsu-san didn't mean to do any harm.

253
00:17:17,130 --> 00:17:20,600
If he meant it, that'd make it even worse!

254
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:27,270
Stuff happens in life, you know, Natsu?

255
00:17:28,270 --> 00:17:31,180
That's not cheering me up, Happy.

256
00:17:31,180 --> 00:17:33,940
Plus, this isn't a time for 
your stomach to be growling.

257
00:17:40,030 --> 00:17:41,920
We got spotted again.

258
00:17:42,540 --> 00:17:43,950
What'll we do?

259
00:17:43,950 --> 00:17:45,410
Um...

260
00:17:45,410 --> 00:17:49,260
We are travelers who have lost our way!

261
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:50,080
P...

262
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:53,570
Please forgive us!

263
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:58,880
Oh great Exceed, please spare our lives!

264
00:17:58,880 --> 00:18:00,610
Exceed?

265
00:18:00,610 --> 00:18:02,390
I wonder who they're talking about?

266
00:18:04,390 --> 00:18:05,780
Um...

267
00:18:05,780 --> 00:18:07,350
Don't, Natsu!

268
00:18:07,350 --> 00:18:09,230
We can't exactly fix things up now, right?

269
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:13,000
Uh, we have something we'd like to ask you!

270
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,900
Our friends are here in Edolas, and...

271
00:18:16,030 --> 00:18:19,100
Save us!

272
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:20,200
Oh, for cryin' out loud...

273
00:18:21,750 --> 00:18:26,890
When those people saw Carla and Happy, 
it seemed like they were frightened...

274
00:18:26,890 --> 00:18:29,340
See? It wasn't my fault.

275
00:18:29,340 --> 00:18:32,450
Was I making that scary a face?

276
00:18:32,710 --> 00:18:34,010
Maybe they thought you'd eat them!

277
00:18:34,010 --> 00:18:36,050
Aw, I'm not <i>that</i> hungry.

278
00:18:38,940 --> 00:18:40,140
What is it now?

279
00:18:40,140 --> 00:18:41,930
I have a bad feeling about this.

280
00:18:52,150 --> 00:18:53,650
We fell again...

281
00:18:53,650 --> 00:18:54,820
Sheesh...

282
00:18:57,190 --> 00:18:58,680
Where are we?

283
00:18:58,680 --> 00:19:01,260
It looks like a storehouse of some kind...

284
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:05,300
I don't know how much good it'll do now,

285
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:09,030
but let's borrow some clothes 
for disguises from here.

286
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:16,070
There's tons of fun clothes!

287
00:19:16,070 --> 00:19:18,810
Natsu-san, don't look over here, okay?

288
00:19:18,810 --> 00:19:20,720
Take a look at me!

289
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:23,020
I guess this'll do.

290
00:19:23,020 --> 00:19:24,250
How cute!

291
00:19:24,250 --> 00:19:27,010
You look good in anything, Carla.

292
00:19:31,020 --> 00:19:32,720
What is it?

293
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:35,790
It's Fairy Tail!

294
00:19:36,610 --> 00:19:39,320
The building's a little 
different, but it's Fairy Tail!

295
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:40,440
It's gotta be!

296
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:41,180
Natsu-san!

297
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:42,210
Wait!

298
00:19:42,210 --> 00:19:43,670
Sheesh...

299
00:19:43,670 --> 00:19:45,410
This helmet is heavy...

300
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:05,870
Everyone's safe!

301
00:20:05,870 --> 00:20:07,960
We found everyone pretty easily!

302
00:20:07,960 --> 00:20:10,740
The guild seems really different, though.

303
00:20:10,740 --> 00:20:12,550
Don't worry about the details, man!

304
00:20:12,550 --> 00:20:14,270
Can we really, though?

305
00:20:14,270 --> 00:20:17,360
Wait... This isn't right...

306
00:20:17,780 --> 00:20:20,670
Hey, that's the Request Board...

307
00:20:21,020 --> 00:20:22,820
There's nothing weird at all, see?

308
00:20:22,820 --> 00:20:26,330
So why are we sneaking around like this?

309
00:20:26,330 --> 00:20:27,890
Look carefully.

310
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:31,040
That's...

311
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:34,030
Juvia is going on a job now.

312
00:20:34,030 --> 00:20:35,230
Be careful, now.

313
00:20:35,230 --> 00:20:37,790
W-Wait, Juvia-chan!

314
00:20:39,030 --> 00:20:42,740
I wish you'd take me with 
you... or something...

315
00:20:42,740 --> 00:20:44,340
You're so smothering...

316
00:20:44,340 --> 00:20:46,040
How many layers do you have on?

317
00:20:47,560 --> 00:20:50,340
Strip down a little and 
call me again sometime.

318
00:20:50,340 --> 00:20:51,770
But I get chilled easily!

319
00:20:51,770 --> 00:20:54,560
Gray's way too clingy.

320
00:20:54,560 --> 00:20:57,980
Men in love sure get fired up.

321
00:20:57,980 --> 00:21:00,360
What the heck?!

322
00:21:00,360 --> 00:21:02,650
That's pitiful, Elfman.

323
00:21:02,650 --> 00:21:04,910
You screwed up on a job, again?

324
00:21:04,910 --> 00:21:06,490
I'm so embarrassed...

325
00:21:06,490 --> 00:21:08,560
Who do you think's gonna pick up the slack?

326
00:21:07,250 --> 00:21:10,850
Hey, look! The two vying for 
the strongest in Fairy Tail,

327
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:09,790
I'm sorry..

328
00:21:09,790 --> 00:21:12,310
Don't just apologize!

329
00:21:10,850 --> 00:21:13,090
Jet and Droy, are lecturing Elfman again.

330
00:21:13,090 --> 00:21:14,330
Hope they go easy on him...

331
00:21:14,330 --> 00:21:16,070
Work, work!

332
00:21:16,070 --> 00:21:17,850
Nab works way too much.

333
00:21:17,850 --> 00:21:18,850
You can say that again.

334
00:21:18,850 --> 00:21:21,470
Cana-san, why don't you have 
a drink with us for a change?

335
00:21:21,470 --> 00:21:23,950
Come over here!

336
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:27,220
I know I have spoken of this before to you.

337
00:21:27,220 --> 00:21:30,240
I cannot handle drinking alcohol.

338
00:21:31,150 --> 00:21:32,570
Bis Bis...

339
00:21:32,570 --> 00:21:36,200
What is it, Al Al...

340
00:21:37,060 --> 00:21:38,950
Now look here, you...

341
00:21:38,950 --> 00:21:40,900
But... But!

342
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:42,520
Don't cry at every little thing!

343
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:45,810
I love Juvia-chan!

344
00:21:45,810 --> 00:21:47,020
Shut up, Gray!

345
00:21:47,020 --> 00:21:48,500
And slim down a little!

346
00:21:48,500 --> 00:21:51,070
W-What's going on here?

347
00:21:51,870 --> 00:21:54,240
Everyone's acting really weird!

348
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:58,240
Hey.

349
00:21:58,240 --> 00:21:59,970
Who the hell are you?

350
00:22:02,520 --> 00:22:03,810
No way...

351
00:22:04,040 --> 00:22:04,880
It's...

352
00:22:07,410 --> 00:22:10,430
What the hell are you doing 
sneaking around under there?

353
00:22:10,430 --> 00:22:12,380
Lucy!

354
00:22:12,380 --> 00:22:13,810
...-san?!

355
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:20,850
What in the world is happening?

356
00:23:55,990 --> 00:23:57,320
What's this?

357
00:23:57,320 --> 00:23:59,710
Everyone's personality has gone funky!

358
00:23:59,710 --> 00:24:01,320
Maybe it's the effect of Edolas.

359
00:24:01,320 --> 00:24:03,440
It's like everyone's 
personalities are reversed!

360
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:08,170
Gray wears too much clothing, Elfman's 
a crybaby, and Levy's a bad-girl!

361
00:24:08,170 --> 00:24:09,420
This is hilarious!

362
00:24:09,420 --> 00:24:13,510
If everyone's personality is backwards, 
what will Erza be like, I wonder?

363
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:16,510
Next time: Fairy Hunting.

364
00:24:16,510 --> 00:24:19,280
The opposite of brutal, 
violent Erza would be...

365
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:20,130
I dunno, what?

366
00:24:20,130 --> 00:24:24,850
She'll probably say "Welcome back, 
Master!" or something like that.

